@MaligneRange although you've raised an interesting point. They've actually renamed every member of the othopoxvirus genus following a new naming convention. Other virus families have followed this convention already, e.g. Orthoflavivirus denguei or Alphainfluenzavirus influenzae.
:Up until now, this page has said that the ICTV is responsible for naming viruses. But it appears that they don't decide the common-usage name, just the taxonomic name.
:So there's a case for renaming this article "mpox virus" instead of "monkeypox virus".

